OL,3,C'I feel brilliant!': Burma veteran
OL,4,Ccelebrates 103rd birthday
OL,6,FWhen asked what the secret was to a
OL,7,Flong life, he said: "Thinking of your
OL,8,Fhealth all the time and what you're
OL,9,Fdoing. Don't indulge in things that
OL,10,Fyou feel are not healthy for you, and
OL,11,Ftry to get exercise - eat the right
OL,12,Ffood and sleep."
OL,14,FReflecting on his life, Mr Fenton
OL,15,Fspoke of his time in conflict in
OL,16,FBurma, saying he feels "extremely
OL,17,Flucky" to have lived as long as he has.
