OL,3,C'I feel brilliant!': Burma veteran
OL,4,Ccelebrates 103rd birthday
OL,6,FReflecting on conflict, Mr Fenton
OL,7,Fsaid: "Even though we had this war
OL,8,Fthat we were involved in, when in my
OL,9,Fyounger days I could have been in
OL,10,Fenjoying life. Unfortunately the same
OL,11,Fthings are more or less happening
OL,12,Ftoday!
OL,14,F"You've got wars raging around the
OL,15,Fplace, and you never know what's going
OL,16,Fto happen - it's dreadful!"
OL,18,FHe concluded by saying he hopes the
OL,19,Fyounger generations can learn from his
OL,20,Fexperiences of war.
